[Foreboding music]

00:46.910 --> 00:49.340
Man: I was up a
couple of weeks ago

00:49.350 --> 00:50.840
and the whole area
was flooded.

00:50.850 --> 00:53.980
Couldn't even get in
past the gate.

00:54.180 --> 00:57.480
You gotta be careful of the
weather up this way. Yeah.

00:57.490 --> 00:58.350
About a week ago,

00:58.350 --> 01:00.020
just north of here? Snow.

01:00.220 --> 01:01.690
Everything covered
for four days.

01:01.690 --> 01:03.520
And then it flooded down here.

01:03.530 --> 01:06.530
So, like that, we'd have to
bring the truck in.

01:06.530 --> 01:09.560
But I'm not supposed to be
doing that on my own.

01:10.630 --> 01:13.130
Walking like this, these
conditions? No problem.

01:13.270 --> 01:17.240
But, if I get stuck in here, now
with the truck or the ATV?

01:18.370 --> 01:19.940
Maybe get hurt or something,
you know?

01:20.410 --> 01:21.740
I'm in shit with the daughter.

01:26.220 --> 01:29.280
Make sure, now, everybody
got the right clothing.

01:29.290 --> 01:33.020
'Cause, you know, you'd catch
your death up here.

01:33.160 --> 01:35.990
Yeah. Well, I don't think
I'll be that lucky.

01:38.730 --> 01:40.630
What are you calling it, again?

01:40.900 --> 01:42.530
Incredible Violence.

01:46.900 --> 01:48.100
Well, there it is.

01:49.110 --> 01:52.340
Full basement and three stories.

01:52.910 --> 01:55.040
If we don't sell it
out from under you-

01:55.040 --> 01:57.780
It's yours to use.

01:59.080 --> 01:59.980
Looks good.

02:01.280 --> 02:03.420
And no one is around?

02:03.790 --> 02:05.090
Take a look.

02:05.420 --> 02:07.320
You can scream blue
murder out here.

02:07.320 --> 02:10.990
There's not a neighbour
around to hear you.

02:10.990 --> 02:12.860
Sounds good.

02:15.900 --> 02:16.930
How about inside?

02:19.400 --> 02:20.670
[Bang}

02:21.870 --> 02:23.140
Ooof!

02:28.740 --> 02:30.580
She's stuck.

02:38.850 --> 02:40.650
[Bang, bang]

02:42.460 --> 02:44.360
After the flood,
she's all swollen.

02:47.200 --> 02:49.100
So, is this happening, or...

02:53.800 --> 02:55.570
Between the doors
and the windows, now.

02:56.770 --> 02:58.170
I think you need a crowbar...

02:59.410 --> 03:00.810
and a crooked woman

03:00.810 --> 03:03.080
just to get into this house.

03:04.850 --> 03:06.380
[Bang, bang]

03:06.850 --> 03:09.520
Come on we go see
what's in the shed.

03:11.050 --> 03:13.550
[From the shed] The
daughter's gonna be so excited

03:13.560 --> 03:15.290
when she hears you're
making a horror movie

03:15.290 --> 03:16.660
in her childhood home.

03:17.290 --> 03:20.030
She's a real fan of that stuff.

03:20.030 --> 03:21.700
I guess you'll
recognize the house

03:21.700 --> 03:24.670
when it comes out
in the movie?

03:25.270 --> 03:27.730
What are you calling it again?

03:28.640 --> 03:30.440
Invisible Violence.

03:30.810 --> 03:32.440
I'll have to write
that down now,

03:32.440 --> 03:34.510
so I remember when
it comes out.

03:34.640 --> 03:35.410
Who knows,

03:35.410 --> 03:36.610
you might even come up with

03:36.610 --> 03:39.410
a better name for it by then.

03:40.320 --> 03:42.420
Are you looking for a couple
of dead people?

03:42.420 --> 03:45.950
Myself and the daughter
would love to be a part of it.

03:45.960 --> 03:47.990
Just to see how you
make it all happen.

03:47.990 --> 03:49.590
[Whispering]
I am a vessel.

03:49.590 --> 03:52.190
- She'd be really pleased if you
could accommodate her.

03:52.900 --> 03:55.330
- I'm not saying you got to.
- I am the vessel

03:55.970 --> 03:57.260
- You can still have the house.

03:57.270 --> 03:59.400
I'm not the sort of fella
who'd give something,

03:59.400 --> 04:01.400
expecting something
in return, you know.

04:02.670 --> 04:05.740
Now where did I put
that thing again, now?

04:06.140 --> 04:08.410
¶¶¶¶
[Electronic music]

04:08.410 --> 04:10.010
There it is! Alright.

04:10.610 --> 04:11.710
[Phone buzzes]

04:11.710 --> 04:12.680
[Glass tips over]

04:12.680 --> 04:13.850
[Phone buzzes]

04:18.750 --> 04:19.649
I don't know.

04:19.790 --> 04:21.390
I don't know what
I'm gonna do.

04:23.530 --> 04:25.130
Man: How much was it for?

04:26.200 --> 04:27.960
They gave me two hundred
and fifty k.

04:28.530 --> 04:29.830
- [Whistles]

04:29.830 --> 04:31.600
How much is left?

04:37.040 --> 04:38.440
What did you spend it on?

04:38.810 --> 04:39.740
- I don't know.

04:40.680 --> 04:41.840
It went here and there.

04:41.840 --> 04:45.010
- You spend a quarter of a
million dollars here and there?

04:45.010 --> 04:47.110
- It was sitting in my bank
account for months.

04:47.680 --> 04:49.750
I was supposed to make
the movie months ago.

04:49.750 --> 04:52.890
I just put it off and I put
it off and I put it off.

04:52.890 --> 04:54.090
Anyway...

04:54.990 --> 04:56.090
It's gone now.

04:56.690 --> 04:57.990
That's that.

05:00.630 --> 05:03.900
- So what's gonna happen to you?

05:03.900 --> 05:05.300
- I think it's fraud.

05:05.600 --> 05:06.830
Isn't it?

05:07.070 --> 05:08.370
- Yeah, Patrick.

05:09.270 --> 05:11.000
It's major league fucking fraud.

05:12.310 --> 05:13.540
Who lent you the money?

05:16.950 --> 05:18.510
- I'm not real sure.

05:19.420 --> 05:21.350
- You're not that sure.

05:21.350 --> 05:23.620
- It's like... a group
of investors.

05:26.590 --> 05:27.550
You know, like...

05:29.120 --> 05:30.520
Like a group.

05:33.830 --> 05:34.860
An organization.

05:38.600 --> 05:41.500
- Like a legal organization?

05:44.040 --> 05:44.940
Are you serious?

05:47.040 --> 05:48.340
- Now that you mention it.

05:48.940 --> 05:50.280
It was all very creepy.

05:53.380 --> 05:54.650
- You're gonna die, man.

05:55.050 --> 05:56.520
These people are gonna kill you.

05:58.920 --> 06:00.390
- Makes sense.

06:01.690 --> 06:02.760
I thought they'd do.

06:08.500 --> 06:10.830
- Can you get people to
work on it for free?

06:11.230 --> 06:14.430
- Actors, yes, absolutely.

06:15.040 --> 06:16.940
Those people would
do anything for free.

06:19.010 --> 06:20.710
Crew, though?

06:22.140 --> 06:25.150
For a horror movie,
you need stunts, makeup.

06:25.850 --> 06:26.910
Special effects.

06:28.250 --> 06:30.150
Lights and sound, camera.

06:32.020 --> 06:33.150
Wardrobe, makeup.

06:33.160 --> 06:36.260
Free is not a
realistic option.

06:42.330 --> 06:44.400
[Sighs] This is awful.

06:47.200 --> 06:49.770
Do you know, I was
gonna be a lawyer?

06:50.340 --> 06:52.270
I decided last year.

06:53.180 --> 06:54.710
I was gonna write the exam.

06:55.110 --> 06:56.380
Gonna be lawyer.

06:58.410 --> 07:00.550
But I got that money.

07:03.120 --> 07:05.090
I should have turned it down.

07:07.860 --> 07:10.490
