12:19.100 --> 12:20.070
<i>The Milgram Group.</i>

12:21.170 --> 12:22.800
<i>Let us entertain you.</i>

12:24.410 --> 12:26.370
Welcome to this week's episode

12:26.370 --> 12:27.870
of "Celebrity Autopsy".

12:28.340 --> 12:30.210
It's so great to see
you all again.

12:30.480 --> 12:32.410
This week we have another
fantastic episode

12:32.410 --> 12:35.050
in which we celebrate celebrity.

12:35.050 --> 12:38.890
We will be performing a live,
in-studio autopsy

12:38.890 --> 12:41.590
of a really famous celebrity.

12:41.590 --> 12:43.290
He is an internet star.

12:43.730 --> 12:44.820
A rapper.

12:45.430 --> 12:46.660
And an international movie star.

12:47.930 --> 12:49.400
He is "The Killa".

12:50.100 --> 12:51.330
The rise from internet star

12:51.330 --> 12:54.270
to star of the silver screen
came quickly for The Killa.

12:57.010 --> 12:58.300
All that you've done for me.

12:59.670 --> 13:01.410
You changed my life, truly.

13:03.150 --> 13:05.150
This means so much more
to me this time.

13:06.450 --> 13:07.850
I don't know why.

13:08.580 --> 13:10.880
I think the first time
I hardly felt it.

13:11.320 --> 13:12.890
Because it was so new.

13:17.360 --> 13:19.930
I owe a lot to my players...

13:21.200 --> 13:22.500
To the cast.

13:23.870 --> 13:26.870
To Lindsay and John and Danny.

13:27.440 --> 13:29.440
And Ed, and Amy.

13:30.410 --> 13:33.710
And my little friends Jamie
and Yankton.

13:35.540 --> 13:38.080
I owe a lot to my family.

13:38.510 --> 13:40.180
For holding me together.

13:40.180 --> 13:42.070
And loving me.

13:42.070 --> 13:43.950
And having patience in
this obsession of mine.

13:47.960 --> 13:50.760
But I want to say
thank you to you.

13:52.160 --> 13:54.190
I haven't had an
orthodox career.

13:54.460 --> 13:57.200
And I've wanted more than
anything to have your respect.

13:59.630 --> 14:02.300
The first time I didn't feel it.

14:02.840 --> 14:04.170
But this time, I feel it.

14:05.540 --> 14:08.410
And I can't deny the fact
that you like me.

14:08.980 --> 14:10.410
You really like me.

14:10.850 --> 14:11.910
[Bang]

14:14.280 --> 14:15.280
What are you doing?

14:15.280 --> 14:17.220
Ginger: I don't have a light.
Do you?

14:17.520 --> 14:18.820
- No, you know I don't.

14:19.690 --> 14:21.450
- Then I'll have to
be resourceful.

14:21.620 --> 14:22.720
Did I wake you?

14:23.160 --> 14:24.390
- No, I was still up.

14:27.430 --> 14:28.630
- That's very un-Grace.

14:29.430 --> 14:31.300
Very ungraceful.

14:34.600 --> 14:35.670
There's nothing in here
but booze.

14:39.140 --> 14:40.970
You missed out tonight.

14:41.480 --> 14:43.140
There was a closing party
for some play.

14:43.880 --> 14:45.350
Nothing was free, obviously.
It was theatre.

14:45.350 --> 14:47.210
But there were some
people there.

14:47.480 --> 14:49.620
Apparently, there's new show
starting soon.

14:52.390 --> 14:54.590
I might be able to get you in.

14:55.290 --> 14:56.620
But the spots might be filled.

14:56.760 --> 14:58.590
That's why you need
to come with me.

14:59.660 --> 15:01.530
Oh, I'm doing ok.

15:05.700 --> 15:07.370
What's going on here?

15:08.540 --> 15:09.470
What do you mean?

15:09.470 --> 15:12.740
I mean, it's past nine o'clock
on a school night.

15:12.740 --> 15:14.240
And not only are you still up.

15:14.240 --> 15:15.380
But you wanna drink?

15:15.380 --> 15:16.880
Can't I just have a drink?

15:17.310 --> 15:19.650
Hmmm. There's something
going on here.

15:22.920 --> 15:24.380
I got cast in a movie!

15:26.450 --> 15:27.490
What movie?

15:27.490 --> 15:30.720
Um, the horror film I auditioned
for a few weeks back?

15:31.690 --> 15:32.860
Incredible Vikings?

15:33.190 --> 15:35.030
Incredible Violence.

15:35.560 --> 15:36.930
Who's directing?

15:36.930 --> 15:39.070
G. Patrick Condom.

15:39.070 --> 15:40.370
Condom? I've never heard of him.

15:40.370 --> 15:42.370
Don... Con-DON.
With and N.

15:43.670 --> 15:45.140
What studio is producing it?

15:46.470 --> 15:48.310
Why are you acting like this?

15:48.910 --> 15:50.910
Because I'm an actor.

15:50.910 --> 15:52.180
C'mon.

15:52.180 --> 15:53.250
I'm sorry. It's a habit.

15:53.680 --> 15:55.580
Seriously, though. What studio?

15:55.580 --> 15:58.550
There is no studio.
It's not like that.

15:58.550 --> 15:59.750
It's an art film.

16:02.160 --> 16:03.290
[Laughing] It's an art film?

16:04.390 --> 16:05.860
Sorry I got jealous.

16:07.660 --> 16:08.730
What does that mean?

16:10.000 --> 16:11.130
Let's just drop it, okay.

16:11.130 --> 16:12.770
No. You can't just say
something like that,

16:12.770 --> 16:14.230
and expect me to drop it.

16:14.240 --> 16:15.940
- God, you're so dramatic.

16:16.810 --> 16:18.500
I've never heard of this guy.

16:19.010 --> 16:21.310
I bet you won't know any
of the actors in there.

16:21.310 --> 16:23.280
And it's an independent
art movie.

16:24.080 --> 16:24.980
So?

16:24.980 --> 16:27.750
I can't wait to console you
every night when you come home.

16:27.920 --> 16:29.680
Well, you're not gonna
have to do that.

16:29.680 --> 16:31.880
Because I'm to coming
home at the end of each night.

16:31.890 --> 16:33.450
Not until we're done
filming, anyways.

16:33.890 --> 16:35.590
Oh?

16:35.790 --> 16:36.690
Why is that?

16:36.690 --> 16:40.260
Because we have to stay on set
through the duration of filming.

16:41.930 --> 16:43.660
[Laughs]

16:43.930 --> 16:46.530
No. We're in a house.

16:46.530 --> 16:48.330
A big, nice house. It's...

16:48.340 --> 16:50.170
Stop laughing.

16:51.770 --> 16:52.870
Are you even getting paid?

16:55.210 --> 16:57.580
I think so. I didn't ask.

16:59.350 --> 17:01.410
You have to see what's
gong on here.

17:04.520 --> 17:05.450
It's some student film.

17:05.450 --> 17:07.250
It's gonna be a shit show.

17:07.260 --> 17:09.490
Then you should come with me.

17:09.990 --> 17:12.160
- Not a chance.

17:12.160 --> 17:13.790
I have real auditions
with real films.

17:17.900 --> 17:19.869
Come on!

17:22.400 --> 17:24.300
I was joking about
the real film thing.

17:29.910 --> 17:32.180
I just wish you could
be happy for me.

17:34.280 --> 17:36.450
This could be the
role of a lifetime.

17:36.450 --> 17:40.790
This could change
everything for me.

17:41.760 --> 17:43.360
- Dramatic and sensitive.

17:47.700 --> 17:51.600
You're gonna make
one hell of an actor.

17:51.600 --> 17:53.670
That director has no
idea what he's in for.

17:53.670 --> 17:54.570
[Glasses clink]

